# Git Branching & Timesheet App Updates

This plan covers the transition to a branching workflow and the implementation of the first set of updates from the user's task list.

## 🌳 Git Branching Workflow

We will move away from committing directly to `main`. Instead, we'll use a feature-branch approach.

1.  **Create Branch**: `git checkout -b updates-v2`
2.  **Develop**: Make changes to the code in this branch.
3.  **Local Test**: Open the local [index.html](file:///d:/AI%20Coding%20Projects/AntigravityTimesheetApp/index.html) (or use a local server) to verify changes on your computer.
4.  **Mobile Test**: 
    - We will look into [Firebase Hosting Preview Channels](https://firebase.google.com/docs/hosting/test-preview-deploy) if the app is hosted on Firebase.
    - Alternatively, we can use a local IP address to test on your phone over Wi-Fi.
5.  **GitHub Push**: `git push origin updates-v2` (keeps the work backed up in the cloud).
6.  **Merge**: Once all 15 tasks (or a logical subset) are done and tested, we'll merge `updates-v2` back into `main`.

## 🗓️ Calendar-Style PDF Invoice

The major shift is moving from a list-based PDF to a **Traditional Calendar Grid** (matching the provided photo).

### 🏗️ Proposed Architecture
Instead of relying on a hidden Google Script to generate the PDF, we will implement **Local PDF Generation** (Client-Side).
1.  **Print View**: Create a hidden HTML template that mirrors the manual calendar (7 columns, large boxes).
2.  **Data Injection**: Fill each date box with `Start-End` and `Total Hours` from `localStorage`.
3.  **Totals**: Calculate and display the two pay period subtotals (1-15 and 16-End) at the bottom.
4.  **Export**: Use `jsPDF` + `html2canvas` (or a high-quality `@media print` style) to generate the file.

> [!TIP]
> This approach allows you to see a **live preview** on your phone before you even "Generate" it, making verification much easier.

## 🛠️ Proposed Changes

1.  **[UPDATE] PDF Engine**: Switch to a client-side library for exact layout control.
2.  **[NEW] Grid Component**: Design the printable calendar component in [index.html](file:///d:/AI%20Coding%20Projects/AntigravityTimesheetApp/index.html).
3.  **[UPDATE] Task #1**: Ensure 12hr format is used in the grid cells.
4.  **[NEW] Footer Logic**: Automatic calculation of the $25/hr rate and totals for the two halves of the month.

